# m5_smoothing — client. Stationary observer; bursts screenshots
# every 10 ticks while the host walks past. Each consecutive PNG
# should show the host's mech advancing by a small, consistent
# amount — no pop-back / zigzag.
#
# The new P03 path: snapshot_apply pushes remote-mech pelvis to
# Mech.remote_snap_ring (no immediate position write); each tick
# snapshot_interp_remotes lerps between bracketing entries at
# client_render_time_ms - 100 ms; the renderer's alpha lerp
# smooths between sim ticks for vsync-fast displays.
#
# Burst: every 10 ticks from tick 200 to 600 = 41 PNGs. Plus a
# contact sheet for at-a-glance review.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/m5_smoothing_client
network connect 127.0.0.1:24091
name ClientB

burst smooth from 200 to 600 every 10
contact_sheet sheet cols 6

at 750 end
